properties.name: 146 hunt drive - My home
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall horsham pa 19044I grew up in a suburban neighborhood where everyone knows one another and as a kid there was always a big group of fellow neighborhood children to play with, I think this has played a roll in who i am today because i always had a social aspect in my life and learned early the skill of getting along with and being around other people.

properties.name: 5th place in Kentucky
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall KentuckyAt Nationals In Kentucky my 16u softball team Came in 5th in the nation when i was 14. This affected me because this is really when i started to get schools\' attention for my pitching and looked into for scholarships.

properties.name: Bamboozle
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall EAST RUTHERFORD, New JerseyBamboozle is similar to Warped Tour, both Huge summer tours With tons and tons of bands with nine or so stages all in use at the same time lasting over the span of 3 days. Its an awesome experience especially if you like alot of the music there, you get to see a multiple amount of your favorite artists. I went two out of the three days these 2 past years and both were a great time and fond memories.

properties.name: Columbia College Chicago
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall 600 south michigan ave, Chicago, ILI decided for school I wanted to get out of Horsham and go far to experience somewhere new and exciting, and Chicago is certainly that. I love it in the city and i love that i can go somewhere new every day, where as back home i knew the town inside and out.

properties.name: Disney World
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall Lake Buena Vista, Orlando, FL 32830Disney World is and has been one of my favorite places in the world. I\'m a 6 year old at heart so i enjoy everything about this place. I went when i was a baby, but the first trip i remember was in second grade, and my family has gone at least every other year since then, and i still am not and don\'t believe i ever will be bored of it.

properties.name: Edibles
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall Horsham PaEdibles is a restaurant in Horsham that everyone knows. When you don\'t\' know where to go to eat, you go to Edibles, when your sports team wins, you go to Edibles. In fact every year at the end of the season for every age group that i played little league softball since i was 6, our team party would be at Edibles, along with all the other teams in the league. Even though it changed its location from when i was younger, its still the same Edibles everyone my age and older in my area remembers.

properties.name: Elementary School
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall Horsham PAFrom my first grade teacher Mrs. Class to my fifth grade teacher Mr. Glaze, My experience at my elementary school holds many of my fondest memories. I had 3 teachers out of my 6 years there that really made a mark on my memories as a child and impacted my school experience to the point where i loved school as a child.

properties.name: First Cd
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall 801 BETHLEHEM PIKE, North Wales, PA, 19454My first CD was just the Single of Britney Spears\' Hit me Baby One More Time when i was 8. I think this plays into who I am because i\'ve always loved music, even if my taste in it has changed.

properties.name: First Pitch at Carpenter Park
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall 19044Carpenter Park is one of the local Baseball/Softball complex\'s where i grew up. When i was 7 years old this is where i first attempted being a pitcher. I threw the ball straight up in the air and after that was determined to learn how to succeed at it. This is part of who I am because this was a start to the majority of my life that was spent towards pitching for a travel softball team.

properties.name: First Say Anything Concert
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall 334 South St, Philadelphia, PAThis was the First time seeing my at the time favorite band in concert. It is still the best show i have ever been to and ever since i have not missed seeing them when they are on tour.

properties.name: First Softball Nationals
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall VirginiaThis was my first Nationals with my Travel softball team when i was 11.

properties.name: First video game experience
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall horsham Pa 19044This is my childhood friend shana\'s house, where I first played a gameboy, which was a start to a secret addiction to video games that i still have today.

properties.name: Jonas Brothers Concert
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall 3601 South Broad St Philadelphia,PANot a lot of people would think that i would, but I do in fact like the Jonas Brothers. While totally different than shows i usually go to, considering they are always at smaller venues and standing room only, the Jonas brothers concert on July 23rd at the Wachovia Center was one of the best concerts I\'ve been to and one of my favorite new memories.

properties.name: Mr. Coleman's Class
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall horsham PaMy favorite class in highschool, and a big reason i\'m in art school now, was my computer graphics class taught by my favorite teacher, Mr. Coleman. not taking it until my junior year, i never thought i\'d be interested in that field of work before this class. I had a great relationship with my teacher and if it wasn\'t for his interesting and creative assignments and the way he presented the skills and made everything learned intriguing to me as a student really made me want to learn more about all the programs and how to do things and become as experienced as i could in this form of art. because of this i took all three computer graphics courses and have the passion to go into it as a career.

properties.name: Ms. Gallagher's Art class
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall horsham PaThese were the 2nd most influential classes for me in highschool, Art Major 2 and Portfolio with Ms. Gallagher. While Art major 1 was kind of a base and learning skills of art type of class, Art major 2 was more of an opportunity to experience many medias and mediums of art, and you also had more options in projects and creativity available. Portfolio was an even greater opportunity to be creative with your work and this is where you picked a concentration, or theme, and created several pieces going with that. These 2 classes were mostly important to me because Ms. Gallagher was all for preparing you for college art courses and treated it as if it was one, and from my experience so far in drawing and 2d design going by what we do and how they are run, she\'s done well.

properties.name: Ocean City New Jersey
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall ocean city new jerseyWhere i\'m from when summer arrives, everyone heads to the jersey shore. My old best friend had a house in Ocean City, so for most of the summers weeks me and my friends would go stay at her house. for awhile it was like a second home, and because of that now whenever i go down the shore i know the area like i live there.

properties.name: Regal Cinema 22
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall warrington, Pa part of a semi-rural suburban area kid/teen\'s entertainment is going to the movies. When in middle school around seven thirty or eight you could find at least half of your grade in the lobby of the Regal Cinema in Warrington, whether they were seeing a movie or not was questionable, but for some reason it was just another hangout place for the bored.

properties.name: Siren Records
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall Doylestown PaLike i\'ve stated before, in Horsham there isn\'t much to do, so alot of my time was spent in a nearby suburb about 10 minutes away called Doylestown. Doylestown has a lot more going on with Main Street covered with shopping boutiques and there is always people out and about, like a mini city itself. There are two little venues, SIren Records and Moose Lodge, where many local bands play, but they also book bigger names too. Alot of my time was spent in those two places seeing friends play or bands i enjoy.

properties.name: Start of Concert going
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall 2201 Arch Street Philadelphia,paWhen i was 13 I went to see The Academy is and The All American Rejects at the Electric factory. This was really my first show where it wasn\'t in an arena, and wasn\'t britney spears or Nsync. I fell in love with the atmosphere and the feeling of being right there up close with the music right in front of you. this was the start to the countless amounts of shows i\'ve been to since, which was a really big part of my freshman and sophomore years of highschool, and I still love going today.

properties.name: Uncle bill's pancake house
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall When Visiting New Jersey its necessary to have breakfast at Uncle Bills. its the best pancakes ever and everyone who knows the Jersey Shore knows Uncle Bills Pancake House. they have them in several locations down there such as Avalon and Sea Isle. Its cheap and delicious. There has never been a time that I have been down the shore and not eaten there at least once.

properties.name: Upper Darby Township
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall 326 Watkins Ave, Upper Darby Twp, PAThis is where i had my first Shut out as a pitcher, which is when you give up 0 hits and 0 runs to the other team, at the age of 11 while playing for our local tournament team.

properties.name: Vacation to Mexico
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall Mexicowhen i was 16 i went to mexico with my family. it was one of my favorite vacations because the resort we stayed at really let you experience the culture and always had something fun and entertaining going on from pool games, to volleyball, to shows and performances at night. It is just a fond memory i have and i would love to go back.

properties.name: Vacation to Punta Cana
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall Punta Canawhen i was 14 my family and I went to Punta Cana in the Dominican Republic. This was the first time Being out of the Country for me.

properties.name: bob's beachside Grill
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall ocean city new jerseyBob\'s is where some of the best burgers ever are located in ocean city new jersey. When i used to spend summers down the shore at my friends shore house, we\'d always walk up from the beach to bobs. they were family friends of her family, and her sister worked there from time to time. so for us it was a little hang out we could go to for a break from the sun.

properties.name: south street
properties.description: Posted by Nikkinuttall philadelphia PaDue to the lack of exciting things to do in Horsham, once my best friend could drive, we spent alot of time on South Street, which is a main street in philly. There\'s alot of shopping and food, and its just a nice place to walk around. Also the TLA or Theater of Living Arts is located on South street, which is my favorite Venue in Philly to see bands, and where most of my weekends and occasional weeknights were spent.
